        "content": "<p>The <code>calc</code> block works well enough, but as I was getting used to that style of reasoning, for a long time it felt like squeezing my brain through a straw, setting aside a tool I've used in math, which might be called equational reasoning, where step-by-step operations are done to both sides of an equation. I just thought I'd throw this out there in case it's interesting, it might not be hard to implement - at least in my estimation, a fancy macro might be able to convert <code>eqre</code> into <code>calc</code> (however my macro-fu is nowhere close yet).</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\">-- localized code formatting could align the relations</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">eqre</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- equational reasoning block, for 'both side' operations.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                  </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">              </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">              </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                  </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                      </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- delay these proofs until after the eqre block to declutter?</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">div_right</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- or whatever</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">mul_comm</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">something_assoc</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">div_self</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mul_one</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- there is a calc equivalent by subtracting the left hand side over to the</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- right to form:  0 = rhs - lhs</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><s